Eric Cantona has had 20 years to forgive, forget or apologise for the kung-fu kick at Selhurst Park which saw the Frenchman transformed from maverick to madman — but, fittingly, he will not have a bit of it.

Two decades after that moment of insanity, when Cantona launched himself over the advertising hoardings to attack a Crystal Palace fan, he simply said: ‘I didn’t punch him strong enough. I should have punched him harder.’

Anyone who remembers the incident or remembers Cantona, will not be in the least bit surprised by his recollections of one of the most seismic events in Premier League history. 

