Even today, Cantona, 48, sees the episode as a piece of theatre. ‘I played that moment, at Selhurst Park,’ he said, in an interview with FourFourTwo magazine. 

‘It was a drama and I was an actor. I do things seriously without taking myself seriously. I think Nike found that side of my character and used it very well. Even when I kicked the fan, it’s because I don’t take myself seriously.

‘I didn’t think that I had a responsibility not to do it because of who I was. No, I was just a footballer and a man. I don’t care about being some sort of superior person. I just wanted to do whatever I wanted to do. 

'If I want to kick a fan, I do it. I’m not a role model. I’m not a superior teacher, telling you how to behave. I think the more you see, the more you realise that life is a circus.’

He was banned from English football by the FA for eight months and ordered to carry out community service

